## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Launch EC2 Instance

* Created an Amazon Linux EC2 instance.
* Configured Security Group to allow:

  * SSH (22)
  * HTTP (80)

### Step 2: Install Apache Web Server

Commands executed:

sudo dnf update -y

sudo dnf install httpd -y

sudo systemctl start httpd

sudo systemctl enable httpd

Created a sample web page:

echo "Autoscaling" | sudo tee /var/www/html/test.html

Verified application:

curl http://localhost/test.html

Output:

Autoscaling

---

### Step 3: Create Custom AMI

Created an Amazon Machine Image (AMI) named:

server2

Purpose:

* Preserve application configuration.
* Use the AMI for launching identical instances through Auto Scaling.

---

### Step 4: Create Launch Template

Launch Template Name:

AutoScaling-LT

Configuration:

* AMI: server2
* Instance Type: t2.micro
* Security Group: Web Server Security Group
* Key Pair: Existing SSH Key

Purpose:

* Standardized EC2 launch configuration for Auto Scaling.

---

### Step 5: Create Target Group

Target Group Name:

autoscaling-tg

Configuration:

* Target Type: Instance
* Protocol: HTTP
* Port: 80

Health Check:

Protocol: HTTP

Path: /test.html

Success Code: 200

---

### Step 6: Create Application Load Balancer

Load Balancer Name:

autoscaling-alb

Configuration:

* Internet-facing
* HTTP Listener on Port 80
* Associated with Target Group: autoscaling-tg

Purpose:

* Distribute incoming traffic across healthy EC2 instances.
* Improve availability and fault tolerance.

---

### Step 7: Register Targets

Registered EC2 instances into Target Group.

Verified target health status:

Healthy

---

### Step 8: Create Auto Scaling Group

Auto Scaling Group Name:

autoscaling-asg

Configuration:

Minimum Capacity: 2

Desired Capacity: 2

Maximum Capacity: 5

Attached Target Group:

autoscaling-tg

Health Checks:

* EC2
* ELB

Result:

Two EC2 instances launched automatically and registered successfully.

---

### Step 9: Configure Auto Scaling Policy

Policy Type:

Target Tracking Scaling Policy

Metric:

Average CPU Utilization

Target Value:

60%

Purpose:

* Automatically launch additional instances when CPU utilization exceeds threshold.
* Automatically terminate excess instances when traffic decreases.

